Add a Base Station Channel (if required)

1. Using a smart device, connect to the GPS via Wi-Fi, with 'abcdeabcde' as the password.
2. Navigate to the IP address 192.168.142.1 in a web browser

3. Select 'Radio' to expand the menu and then 'Radio Configuration'

4. Scroll down to 'General Configuration Management' to ascertain the current channel. In this scenario it it 462.98750 MHz

5. Ensure that 'Wireless Mode' is set to TRIMTALK v1 at 4800 bps
6. If the desired channel is not available to select, scroll down to 'Receive-only Channel Management', tap in the 'Add Channel' toggle, add the required channel and click OK

Set Input/Output Configuration

1. Navigate to 'I/O Configuration' and and 'Port Configuration'

2. Choose 'Bluetooth 1', 'NMEA' and check the toggle to "Maintain configuration when connection dropped".

3. Ensure the NMEA sentences being returned include the following attributes at the correct update intervals:
#### - GGA: 10 Hz
#### - GST: 10 Hz

Establish correct COM port

1. Open the start bar, type 'Blue' and select the best match: 'Bluetooth and other devices settings'

2. Check that the GNSS receiver has been 'added'. In this example, the receiver being connected to has a S/N ending in 00021.

2. a) If the receiver has not been added, ensure that Bluetooth is on, click on the 'Add Bluetooth or other device' icon and follow the wizard to add the desired device.

3. Click on 'More Bluetooth options'

…which will open a Bluetooth Settings dialog:

NB: The 'Port' corresponding to the receiver with 'COM1' in it's name in the 'Outgoing' direction is the port number that will be passed to 12d Field.

NB: In the above case the 'COM9' what what was being used when connecting to a different receiver. COM25 would be selected to use the SPS986 receiver with S/N ending in 00021.
